### Analysis of Leadership Patterns

- **Adaptive leaders** (reflecting more complicated mixture of passive and aggressive masculinity) have been advocates of fairness and the politics of inclusion, irrepressible in wake of failure
- With single exception of **Andrew Jackson**, all leaders listed in Figure 12-8 rank among most expert and credentialed of American political figures

### Occupational Patterns by Generational Type

- Each generational type (and each generation) has included individuals who have made important achievements in every realm of human endeavor
- Most influential members of eighteen generations batched by careers reveal striking patterns (Figure 12-9)

**American history dominated by:**
- **Idealist thinkers** (intellectual/philosophical leadership)
- **Reactive risk-takers** (bold, entrepreneurial action)
- **Civic doers** (collective action and institution-building)
- **Adaptive improvers** (reform and refinement)

- This pattern offers clues about enduring [continues on next page]

