### Generational Responses to the Coming Crisis

**Silent Generation** will participate eagerly in the search for institutional solutions that *work*, channeling their juniors toward solutions that should be *fair* as well

**Boomers** (first-wave cohorts):
- Frowning on the "Golden Age" sales brochures
- Beginning to arrive by mail, will turn up their moral megaphones to full blast
- Many will think: "If ever there were a time to turn Pepperland into reality, that time is nearing"
- On the brink of midlife, will sense their party boat drifting toward a waterfall
- Will start thinking about which way to leap, and when
- **Millennials** (busy transforming college life) will astound and delight elders with their friendly, optimistic, and team-playing attitude

### The Crisis Era Transition

**Moving into the Crisis era**: History suggests the mood will calm somewhat
- Engilded in the electric air before a storm, perhaps already buffeted by the first shock
- Americans will look toward the future with a new attitude of personal realism and public determination
- **Sense of community will strengthen**, with one set of ideals pulling most political energy into its orbit

**Each generation's role as the full burden of its next phase of life descends**:
- **Elder Boomers**: pragmatic management
- **Midlife 13ers**: teamwork for rising-adult Millennials
- The generational cycle will approach its moment of **maximum opportunity—and danger**

### The "Crisis of 2020"

**Secular crisis-moment** (a-secular crisis—snapping generations into these new roles):
- Will give **Boomers** a chance to thrust their enduring ideals into the core of a new national (perhaps even global) order
- Will give **13ers** a chance to redeem themselves while playing for the ultimate stakes
- Will give **Millennials** a chance to demonstrate civic virtue and triumph over great adversity
- Meanwhile, a new generation of child **Adaptives**, smothered by heavily protective 13er nurture, will cower at the sight of adults doing great deeds

**Enter the "Crisis of 2020"**

### Timing of the Crisis

**When will this crisis come?** The climactic event may not arrive exactly in the year 2020, but it won't arrive much sooner or later

**A cycle is the length of four generations**, or roughly eighty-eight years

**If we plot a half cycle ahead** from the Boom Awakening (finding the forty-fourth anniversaries of Woodstock and the Reagan Revolution):
- We project a crisis lasting from **2013 to 2024**

