### Crisis Timing Projections

- Projecting from **FDR landslide** and **Pearl Harbor** anniversaries → crisis from **2020-2029**
- Projecting from when crisis arrives: **sixty-two years after Idealists' middle birthyear** (early 2020s)
- Peak of crisis: surviving **Silent** in mid-eighties and beyond, **Boomers** in elderhood, **13ers** in midlife, **Millennials** in rising adulthood, new generation of **Adaptives** in youth

### What Will Precipitate the Crisis?

- Could be almost anything, including **old citizens trumped up by generation of elderly warrior-priests**
- Spark may seem accidental—as with many past examples (**Andros**, **Boston Tea Party**, **Lincoln's election**, **Pearl Harbor**)
- Old Idealists may have hand in stirring events to **maximum political effect**, mobilizing younger generations

### Significance of This Crisis

- Recall parallel past: **Glorious Revolution**, **American Revolution**, **Civil War**, years spanning **Great Depression** and **World War II**
- **2020-2029** will be **turning point in American history** and **adrenaline-filled moment of trial**
- At climax, Americans will feel **fate of posterity** hangs in balance

### National Mood During Crisis

- Pivotal moment in lifecycles of all generations alive
- **National mood will be omnipresent**
- **Moral order will be unquestioned**—"rights" and "wrongs" crisply defined and obeyed
- **Sacrifices will be asked, and given**
- America will be **implacably resolved** to do what needs doing, whatever cost

### How the Crisis Will End

- Three of four antecedents ended in **triumph**, fourth (**Civil War**) in mixture of moral fatigue + **weak and vengeful sense of victory**
- Can foresee full range of outcomes: **stirring achievement to apocalyptic tragedy**

### If Crisis Comes Early (Around Year 2000)

- **Year 2000 or soon thereafter** provides **Boomers** occasion to impose "millennial" visions on nation and world
- Very high risk of **cataclysm** during **2000-2009 decade**
- Boomers squarely in **midlife** and nearing peak of political/institutional power
- Exactly where **Transcendentals** were when **John Brown** planning Harper's Ferry raid
- Boomers can best serve civilization by **restraining themselves** (or letting themselves be restrained by others) until twilight years
- Then their spiritual energy finds expression not in midlife leadership but in **elder stewardship**

### Assumed Timeline (Crisis Around 2020)

- Once crisis arrives ~**2020**, once end in view, all generations will **gaze hopefully toward milk and honey**

