### The Intergenerational Deal of circa-2020

- **Two-sided intergenerational bargain**: Boomers receive elder benefits, G.I.s retain moral authority
  - Boomers demand sweeping **moral authority** in exchange for elderhood benefits
  - Will retain national leadership through 2020s, dominance of old-age values and culture
  - **Boom share of Congress and governorships** peaking before 2010, remains dominant plurality into 2020s

- **Boomer political influence peaks late in life**
  - Like Awakener and Missionary predecessors, **Boom leaders will exercise their greatest political influence unusually late in life**
  - Even after governmental tenure expires, they will insist on setting America's cultural and intellectual tone

### Economic and Medical Policy Shifts

- **National income spent on elder medical care may be little changed** despite:
  - Larger Boomer numbers
  - Longer lifespans
  - Huge variety of expensive medical technologies available

- **Boomer personality drives economic policy**:
  - Prefer "**self-care**" to hospital care wherever feasible
  - Elder use of chemical medications will decline
  - Growing reliance on alternative medical approaches (homeopathy to evangelical faith-healing)
  - **Federal health policy will dispense with G.I.-era notion** that elder beneficiaries can privately decide with doctors how much younger taxpayers' income to spend on health care
  - Type and extent of health-care assistance regulated by **tightly regulated social decision**

### Social Security and Medicare Transformation

- Boomers will force dramatic turn in **Social Security politics in 2010s**
- Will bargain for entirely new intergenerational "deal"
- Snapping chain of ever-rising benefits G.I.s insisted would never end
- **Boom leaders will thoroughly recast—and probably rename—Social Security and Medicare**
- To avoid raising burdens on younger generations, leave peers with purchasing power below what G.I.s enjoyed
- Exempting only "deserving" poor from new regime of old-age austerity
- **Affluent Boomers will receive little economic recompense** from lifetime of payroll taxes
- Support others through self-esteem from knowing they are *not* receiving rewards from community

### Cultural and Occupational Changes

- **Occupations associated with the Boom** (education, media, arts) will gray with them
- From university lecterns to news anchor booths to Oval Office
- **America circa 2020 will value the cultural and intellectual tone** Boomers set

