- All their lives, Boomers have been bracing themselves for an **old age of diminished material dependence**
- As 1990s dawn, more than 7/10 Boomers do not think Social Security will help them when old
- G.I.s at like age had doubts about their future; public support would have triggered prompt and effective political action
- But for **inner-fixated Boomers**, this negative expectation simply requires an **adjustment to karma** and is not a great cause for alarm
- No matter how hard life gets, no matter how serious the world's problems, **Boom self-esteem will remain unconquerable**
- Old Aquarians will consider themselves "together" people, sensing their physical mortality and susceptibility to the **fourth dimension (time)**
- Boomers will turn focus to the **fifth—the spiritual**
- Other generations will find this attitude peculiar, even frightening
