### Boomer Leadership and the Intergenerational Deal (circa 2020)

- **Boomers will force dramatic turn** in Social Security politics in the 2010s, creating entirely new intergenerational "deal"
- Will snap chain of ever-rising benefits that **G.I.s insisted would never end**
- Boomers will thoroughly **recast—and probably rename—Social Security and Medicare**
- To avoid raising burdens on younger generations, Boomers will leave peers with **purchasing power below what G.I.s and Silent enjoyed**
- Will exempt "deserving" poor from new regime of **old-age austerity**
- Affluent Boomers will receive little economic recompense from lifetime of payroll taxes paid to support others
- **Self-esteem from knowing they are not receiving rewards from community** in turnabout from G.I. entitlement ethic

### Health Care and Elder Support circa 2020

- **Proportion of national income spent on elder medical care may rise little if at all** despite Boomers' larger numbers, longer lifespans, and expensive medical technologies
- Driven by personality as much as economics, Boomers will prefer **costly "self-care"** to hospital care wherever feasible
- **Elder use of chemical medications will decline**, offset by growing reliance on alternative medical approaches—**from New Age homeopathy to evangelical faith-healing**
- Federal health policy will dispense with G.I.-era notion that elder beneficiaries can privately decide with doctors how much of younger taxpayers' income they want to spend on health care
- Type and extent of health-care assistance old Boomers receive will be **tightly regulated social decision**

### The Two-Sided Intergenerational Compact

- In return for austere elderhood, **Boomers will demand sweeping moral authority**
- Will in all likelihood **retain national leadership** until they reach advanced old age and set their **values firmly locked in place**
