### Boomer Leadership and the Coming Crisis

- The major question: whether Boom leadership will end in triumph or tragedy will hinge on this generation's capacity to restrain (or let others restrain) its latent ruthlessness
- Historical examples of elder Idealists: **William Berkeley**, **Joseph Bellamy**, **William Sherman**, **Douglas MacArthur**
- Aging Idealists have been attracted to words like **"exterminate"** and **"eradicate"** — words of apocalyptic finality
- If the purpose of crisis is **inner principle**, the degree of outer-world destruction needed for those ideals to triumph will be of secondary consideration

> "Make no mistake: Faced with crisis, this generation of onetime draft resisters will not hesitate, as elder warrior-priests, to conscript young soldiers to fight and die for righteous purpose."

### Shop-at-Nothing Zeal

- This **shop-at-nothing zeal** is already apparent in the first Boomer cohorts to reach their mid-forties
- Examples: **Elliott Abrams** and **Oliver North** at one ideological edge to **Mitch Snyder** and **Denis Hayes** at the other
- Picture these individuals as national elders, unclaimed by anyone older — and then realize they represent their generation's **moderate first wave**, whose youth was marked by relatively few (but increasing) social pathologies

### The Evangelical Last-Wavers

- Add in the fiery passion of the more **evangelical last-wavers**
- Sharpen everyone's moral conviction, reduce everyone's level of tolerance, subtract the active presence of any adult Adaptives
- That is the leadership awaiting America, circa 2020
- Easy to picture aging Boomers as noble, self-sacrificing patriarchs — but just as easy to see these righteous Old Aquarians as the worst nightmare that could ever happen to the world

### Spiritual Elders and Methods

- Other generations of spiritualist elders have had visions of apocalypse; this one will have the **methods**
- Had the **Transcendentals** discovered an immensely destructive weapon, they no doubt would have used it to destroy **Richmond** (or **Washington**)
- Lacking such a weapon, the **Missionaries** set loose a smart young Civic generation to invent and build one — which the country was in a mood to use
- The Boom will be the first Idealist generation to enter a crisis with the weapons of **Armageddon** at its immediate command

<!-- p. 408 -->

### Boomer Elderhood: Communal Living and New Values

- Small towns and rural life will appeal to evangelical Boomers as repositories of enduring values, similar to how Bible Belt appealed to Missionaries
- Circa-1990 **New Age camps** scattered throughout American countryside will grow, offering **communal living** and flower-child wayfarers
- Communal living will enable modest means to share expenses in era of reduced pensions, providing emotional support for elders who lack spouses, children, or both
- **Boom's Pepperland** won't bring spiritual rejuvenescence of the 1960s, but will represent collective ratification of Boom values that will seem old to others

### Crisis of 2020: Collective Morality and Global Mission

- By 2010s, aging generation will feel **collective morality** with urgency about unsolved problems in outer world
- Events earlier eliciting compromise/stalemate will now bring aggressive action pursuant to Boom principle
- **The Crisis of 2020**—the Gray Champion's hour of "darkness, and adversity, and peril"—will be at hand
- Old Boomers may attribute crisis to "mistakes" America made by turning back on future during Inner-Driven 1980s and 1990s
- Responding to domestic and international challenges in ways unimaginable today

### Boom Leadership: Global Perfectionism

- Boom leaders will be **policy perfectionists**, inclined to enforce principle even at risk of toppling existing order
- This generation will see in themselves a **global mission**—ethical, ecological, economic, and quite possibly military
- Quest for **righteousness** having been local through rising adulthood and national in midlife—will extend globally in elderhood
- Will define acceptable behavior of other nations narrowly and the appropriate use of American arms broadly
- Unlike old Idealists, Boomers will **not instinctively dislike authoritarian regimes**; indeed, they will be quite authoritarian themselves
- Key question: whether such authority is exercised for good or for evil

### Boomers and Global Authority

- Boomers will find enemies, most likely in new places
- Unlike G.I. fathers, Boomers will have **little interest in a continued U.S.-Soviet rivalry**
- They may see Russia a second superpower useful for maintaining order in ethically disheveled world
- Old Boom far more likely to direct **global wrath at the Third World**
- Quest for environmental asceticism may collide with developing societies prioritizing higher material standard of living
- No matter what air is polluted or forests slashed, **terrorists and drug traders** may or may not still be major problems by 2010s
- Boomers will have grown accustomed to blaming Third World leaders
- Most Third World leaders will be **a generation younger than the Boom**, who by then will associate men in their forties with roguish amorality

### Religious Fundamentalism Threat

- Great peril might arise if Boomers confront **old religious fundamentalists** whose inner zeal matches their own
- The most terrible war in [text continues on next page]

<!-- p. 410 -->

### Entering Post-Elderhood in an Outer-Driven Era (2026-2047)

- **Boomers** will hold power until around the peak of the crisis, then either exit heroically (**Missionary-style**) or be forced out (**Transcendental-style**)
- Having gathered around the drumbeat of **Boomer principle** going into the crisis, younger generations will now want to escape from the stern Boom shadow
- They will want to taste something material, practical, friendly—**something non-Boom**
- As they face this inevitable reaction, old Boomers will also face a temptation that has confronted every aging **Idealist generation** since the **Puritans**: to take their church with them (just as **Civics** are tempted to take their community with them) as they pass beyond their tenure of power
- It is the temptation to believe, like the elder **Missionary** poet **Wallace Stevens** in *Opus Posthumous*, that "**God is in me, or else is not at all**"
- The Boomers will also do what all generations must: **They will die**
- If the end comes easy to no generation, **Idealists** are at least able to see in death a form of **spiritual transcendence**
- The preferred Boomer departure will be one **with a reason, with a meaning**
- Here and there, a few **Don Quixotes** will deliberately link their death to one final stand for principle
- Driven by a mixture of


<!-- p. 409 -->

### Boomer Crisis Leadership: The 2020s Gray Champion

- **Boomer generation** will transform into America's next **Gray Champions** - elders to whom younger generations turn for determination and vision
- Time will be right for a great leader to emerge with "the eye, the face, the attitude of command" like **Abraham Lincoln** or **Franklin Roosevelt**

**Key question**: Whether Boom leadership will end in triumph or tragedy depends on their capacity to restrain or let others restrain its **latent ruthlessness**

**Historical pattern of elder Idealist crisis leaders**:
- **William Berkeley** or **Joseph Bellamy**
- **William Sherman** or **Douglas MacArthur**
- Elder Idealists historically attracted to "exterminative" and "eradicative" words of apocalyptic finality
- When crisis purpose is inner principle, outer-world destruction becomes secondary consideration

**Warning about Boomer crisis behavior**:
- Faced with crisis, this generation of onetime draft resisters will not hesitate as elder warrior-priests
- Will conscript young soldiers to fight and die for righteous purpose
- **Shop-at-nothing zeal** already apparent in first Boomer cohorts reaching mid-forties (from **Elliott Abrams** and **Oliver North** to **Mitch Snyder** and **Denis Hayes**)

**Leadership characteristics emerging circa 2020**:
- National elders unclaimed by anyone older, realizing their generation is **moderate** wave
- Youth marked by relatively few but increasing **social pathologies**
- Fiery passion of evangelical last-wavers sharpens everyone's moral conviction
- Reduces everyone's tolerance level for **subtlety**
- Active presence of any adult **Adaptives** absent - that is the leadership awaiting America

> "It is easy to picture aging Boomers as noble, self-sacrificing patriarchs—but just as easy to see these righteous Old Aquarians as the worst nightmare that could ever happen to the world."

**Contrast with previous Idealist generations**:
- **Transcendentals** had visions of apocalypse but also the **methods** - discovered immensely destructive weapon, would have used it to destroy Richmond or Washington
- **Missionaries** lacked such weapon, set loose smart young **Civic generation** to invent and build one (country was in mood to use)
- **Boom** will be first Idealist generation to enter crisis with weapons of Armageddon at immediate command
