## Completing the Millennial Cycle

### Generational Anxiety and Coming Rivalry
- Serious **13er lobby** articulates anxiety of today's 25-year-olds: whether young adults can ever escape the shadow of the domineering **Boom**
- Nation's next great **generational rivalry** is brewing, ready to bubble over

### Historical Pattern of Generational Feuds
- Throughout American history, nastiest one-apart generational feuds have been **midlife Idealists** and **rising Reactives**
- Historical pattern happened every time:
  - **Puritans vs. Cavaliers**
  - **Awakeners vs. Liberty**
  - **Transcendentals vs. Gilded**
  - **Missionaries vs. Lost**
- **Idealists** invariably view younger **Reactives** as wild, soulless, "bad" generation—while **Reactives** see older **Idealists** as pompous, authoritarian, and (in power) dangerous
- **13ers and Boomers** are already beginning to regard each other this way
- During 1990s, this mutual suspicion will harden

### The "Roar" of the 1920s Repeating
- Last skirmish between oil-and-water types arose just before **World War I**, grew mean after the Armistice, contributed to the "roar" of the **1920s**
- Something like this "roar" lies in America's near-term future

### The Defining Event Prediction
- Cycle suggests that **13ers will suffer an *alienating event*** when their first cohorts are in their **thirties**
- This nasty stroke of history will convince them theirs is a **feckless lifecycle**
- Could be **AIDS** epidemic (has mainly struck the Boom, will ravage 13th if it expands unchecked)
- Could be **diplomat-directed but youth-scourging military campaign**—something on par with **Progressives-led intervention against Kaiser Wilhelm II** or **Enlightener-led war against French Canada**
- Lining up the **13er lifecycle** with Liberty and Lost, such a campaign would occur sometime in the early 1990s
- Most likely: the **alienating event will take the form of an economic downturn**, even brief, will serve the purpose

### Economic Threats for First Wave 13ers
- Economic threats loom heavy on the **13er horizon**
- To begin with, first class graduated from college in **1983**—this generation's aspiring elite yet to confront even mildly harsh conditions in national economy
- Second, never before in American history have **public-benefit "safety nets"** been tilted so heavily toward **retired elders** (no matter how affluent) and away from **rising adults** (no matter how poor)
- **Great majority of 13ers in poverty** are not eligible for a penny in **subsidized health care**
- Many are coming of age with **unprecedented financial burdens**:
  - No previous American generation has arrived in workforce paying such **high tax rates on first dollar of earnings**
  - Bearing such **large high-interest student loans**
  - Facing so many anti-youth **"two-tier" wage and benefit scales**
  - Encountering such **high housing costs relative to income**

### If Economy Weakens: 13ers as Stranded Generation
- If economy weakens, **13ers will feel stranded as a generation**
- Sensing little of the elder goodwill GIs enjoyed through the **Great Depression**
- Nor the public exaltation of youth that buoyed **Boomers** through the stagflated **1970s**
- To their regret, **13ers will find themselves paying a price for generational criticism they endured** (but did not answer) through the 1980s
- Young workers

<!-- p. 411 -->

### Boomers in the 2030s-2050s

- When **year 2030** dawns, Boomers will range in age from **69 to 87**
- Crisis turning will be over; eighty-ish first-wavers will reflect back on well-timed lifecycle
- Person born in late 1940s will recall: growing up indulged, coming of age during flowering time, passing through rising adulthood in consumption/careerism era
- Among Boomers lucky enough to last **eight decades** (more than half of those alive today), second forty years will be memories
- Boomers will have spent midlife in era suited to sober realizations of mature parents and community leaders
- Will have entered old age just as elder wisdom was newly venerated, reached collective deathbeds knowing necessary deeds had been done
- Allowing heirs to live happily ever after (or at least try)
- If this comes to pass, generation may be eulogized as **Franklin Roosevelt** was by **Churchill** for having died "an enviable death"

### Boomer Elders and Millennial Midlife (2050)

- By **year 2050**, America will have very old **Boomer survivors** (twenty-first-century equivalents of **Susan B. Anthony** or **Robert Frost**)
- Celebrated elders will join others in rejoicing over re-emergent secular power of their midlife **Millennial** children
- By mid-2050s, as next Idealist generation comes of age, **three or four million old Aquarians** will remain alive
- More than a few will be on university faculties somewhere, telling tittering young audiences what the **Woodstock 1960s** were like
- Finally—around age 100—getting a chance to see them happen again

### Completing the 13er Diagonal

- The **generational cycle** is a sneaky fortune wheel for a **Reactive generation**
- It spins, it turns—and just when it lets you think you've lost, it tantalizes
- Just when you think you've won, it clicks again, and you've lost
- So will it be for **13ers**

### Entering Rising Adulthood in an Inner-Driven Era (1991-2003)

