### 13er Alienation and Social Burden

- **13ers** will face criticism from elders at homecoming celebrations for soldiers, heightening feelings of alienation
- Will bear major economic and social transition burdens but won't be easily suckered
- Like **"Don't Tread on Me" Liberty** of 1760s, will resist Boomer-led social crusades and seek predictable refuge
- Will avoid complicated abstractions of aging **Silent** and high-minded crusades of **midlife Boomers**
- As Boomers rise to power, 13er voters increasingly antigovernment, endorsing **isolationism** over global crusades

### 13er Cultural and Political Outlook

- Like 1920s-era **Lost Generation**, will take pleasure in revealing elder "lies" in families, communities, national politics
- Will press to **simplify the complex**, narrow the bloated, eliminate the unworkable
- Drawn to blunt, nonsense candidates
- **Thirteener culture** will be far more **ethnically diverse** than Boom's—catapulted Eastern and Southern Europeans to prominence
- Same pattern for **Hispanics and Asians**
- **Chinese democracy movement** and political controversies in Latin America will provide grist for poignant intergenerational clashes
- New ethnic diversity will bring resurgence of youth-propelled racism and **"hate crimes"**

### 13er Class Divisions and Social Problems

- Lacking cultural center of gravity, 13ers of all backgrounds will feel at risk in ways their Boomer and Silent parents did not
- Most secular young ethnic achievers will encounter festering racial hostility from their peers (like **Jewish Lost** in 1920s)
- Most children who grew up poor/unskilled in 1970s-1980s will carry incapacities and pathologies into adulthood
- Through 1990s, unmarried mothers and undereducated of both sexes will remain unemployable (and dependent) in 30s and 40s as they were in teens
- Efforts at **adult remedial education** will be halfhearted and ineffectual

### Crime and Punishment in 13er Era

- Many of today's youth gangsters will ripen into adult facsimile, waging **Capone-style wars** with police (mostly with Boom prosecutors, 13er defenders)
- Older generations will blame nation's problems of crime, drugs, inner cities on 13ers and their treating life as a game
- By late 1990s, as 13ers fill the **crime-prone phase of life**, street crime will be perceived as evil
- Criminal beyond rehabilitation except through sternest of regimes
- Once Boomer judges go to work, 13ers will almost surely become **most permanently warehoused (and executed) generation** in American history
- Many 13ers will defend criminal peers by their ethos: if you're bad and caught, you don't complain about punishment

### Generational Esteem Gap

- **Rising 13ers** sense they will never gain much collective esteem from others
- Americans who today look upon 25-year-olds as wasted bunch will look upon 35-year-olds same way a decade from now
- Any stroke of luck or success will be viewed with suspicion

<!-- p. 414 -->

