<!-- p. 419 -->

### 13ers' Role as Crisis Managers

- **13ers positioned to resist Boomer crisis** - if so, their peers will be best positioned to resist and call the Boom's bluff (like Arthur Vandenberg in 1941)
- **Midlife 13ers will have little influence** on the nature and timing of the Boom's crisis, but will provide the on-site managers and behind-the-scenes facilitators
- Their quick decisions could spell the difference between triumph and tragedy

### Controlling the Boom: 13ers' Fateful Mission

- **Controlling the Boom may emerge as the 13ers' most fateful lifecycle mission**
- Best able to deflect any Boomer drift toward apocalyptic visions
- In an age of rising social intolerance, the very **incorrigibility of midlife 13ers** will be a national blessing
- Task of preventing disaster may fall to life- and liberty-loving **Sixtyeraish fear, or greed** from hard experience
- To tell zealous Boomers to "get real," find calmer solutions that pose fewer risks or limit personal liberty
- A 13er may someday be the **general or Presidential adviser** who prevents some righteous old Aquarian from "loosing the fateful lightning" and turning the world's lights out

### Boom-Millennial Alliance Target

- Those who sustain their alienation into midlife may become targets of a **Boom-Millennial alliance to root out 13er pessimism, fear, or greed** from public life
- Similar to FDR rallying G.I.s against the Lost of "Martin, Barton, and Fish," or Samuel Adams rallying Republicans against Liberty Tories
- Capacity of circa-2020 **50-year-olds to mellow the national mood** will hinge on ability of these two generations to calm their earlier quarrels and build mutual respect
- As they age in place, they will, **like siblings, half remember and half forget** how they behaved toward each other in earlier years

### Getting Less Than Their Share

- Whatever goes wrong in the crisis, **13ers will get more than their share of the blame; whatever goes right, they will get less than their share of the credit**
- Even as 25-year-olds, they know the feeling: "They had better get used to it. When you're Reactive, it comes with the territory."

## Entering Elderhood in an Outer-Driven Era (2026-2047)

### Beginning of Physical Decline (2025)

- Crisis era will hit this generation on the **opening cusp of its era of national leadership** - and the beginning of physical decline
- In 2025, the oldest 13ers will be 64, the youngest 44
- This will have interrupted their **peak earning years**
- Many will be too young to be spared personal sacrifice, too old to start life over again

### Rough and Neglected Old Age Predicted

- **History suggests 13ers will suffer a rough and neglected old age**
- Those who fail to provide for themselves will end up poor, by the standard of the era
- When Boom leaders introduce a **new youth focus into public benefits programs**, 13ers can expect to find themselves **passed over in the transition**
- Those counting on large inheritances from affluent Silent parents may find them sub-
<!-- p. 420 -->

### 13er Economic and Social Outlook

- **13ers** will receive little from older generations: material well-being and economic independence will matter deeply to them, they will cherish what remains rather than seek improvement at youth's expense
- Like elder **Gilded** and **Lost**, 13ers will take wistful pleasure in seeing children succeed and flourish

### 13er Coming of Age Before Crisis

- **13ers** will be the last generation to fully come of age before a history-bending crisis
- They will be perceived as (and feel like) relics from the past, with habits and values rooted in "old regime"
- Will be crusty old conservatives, restraining the young from misguiding human nature through naive overconfidence

### 13er Political Leadership in Mid-2020s

- Around mid-2020s, **13er candidates** will win majority of national leadership posts
- **13er post-crisis Presidents** might be **Washington**, **Grant**, and **Eisenhower**-like: admired for personality than vision
- Like **Gilded** and **Lost**, 13er leaders will distrust debt and inflation as policy instruments
- May keep tax rates high to force the nation to produce more than it consumes—opposite of Boomer-era national choices focused on helping youth
- America will turn energy toward building outer world, not toward cultural depth or spiritual fervor
- Young **Millennials** will fault them for being "do-nothing obstructionists," barriers to execution of the now-lionized Boomers' unfinished moral agenda

### 13er Leadership Style Warning

> "Like Increase Mather, Patrick Henry, and Mark Twain, the most popular 13er elders will warn against the danger of pushing too far and too fast in a cruel world rigged with pitfalls. But younger generations will not listen."

- In an **Outer-Driven era**, can-do Millennials will be too busy coaxing smiles out of their oh-so-adorable **Idealist babies**

<!-- p. 421 -->

### Completing the Millennial Diagonal

- Today's kindergartners may become great **21st-century architects and builders** (from Lego play), **Nobel-laureate scientists** (from lightning bug capture), show **extraordinary talent for teamwork and public service** (from learning "please" and "thank you")
- The **generational cycle** tells us not just to wonder, but to **expect such a destiny** from these kids
- America's mothers and fathers are giving birth to the nation's next great **Civic generation**, inheritors of the tradition of **Cotton Mather, Thomas Jefferson, and John Kennedy**
- History suggests there is concern about how **conditions and crises** they encounter as rising adults will turn out
- These children will ride on the **post-1990 endowment behavior** of the **G.I., Silent, and Boom Generations**

### Entering Youth in an Inner-Driven Era (1991-2003)

**Good news for elders disappointed in 13ers:**

- **Millennials** passing through school will sail smoothly behind a **debris-clearing insistence on quality education and good behavior**
- First impact of **midlife Boomer nurture** felt in **day care and primary grades**
- Throughout the nation's public schools, **Boom teachers and administrators** will join the **Transcendentals and Missionaries** as renowned **middle educators**
- **Silent elders** will be far less inclined than **G.I. elders** to mount **"Proposition 13" rebellions** against school taxes
- In **18 twilight years of Silent leadership**, Congress will repair the **"safety net"** for the benefit of infants and small children
- The ambitious **educational goals** set in 1990 for the year 2000 will be **substantially achieved**

**Educational improvements:**
- From suburbs to inner cities, schools will show **rising aptitude scores**
- American children will gradually **improve their ranking vis-à-vis the Japanese, Europeans, and others** who consistently outscored 13ers

**Social environment contrasts (late 1990s vs. late 1970s):**
- By degrees, the child's world will move toward **greater protection**
- In and out of school, **Millennials will hear a sterner, more resolute adult message** than 13ers ever knew
- **Boomers will crisply define right and wrong**, caring less about a child's opinion than their own (G.I.) parents had cared about the **Beaver's** back in the 1950s
<!-- p. 422 -->

### Millennial Youth Culture Predictions (continued)

- Youth culture will be **more clean-cut and homogeneous** than any seen since circa-1930 **G.I.s**
- By first decade of 21st century, schools will see major shift in learning style:
  - From **MTV-ish "parallel" thinking** back to more logical **"serial" thinking**
  - Computers seen as force for **social individuation** by Boomers/13ers → Millennials will see them as force for **social homogenization**

### Teen Culture Transformation

- **Teen peer leaders** will express growing interest in:
  - Community affairs and collective action
  - Boom regime of get-tough laws and no-kidding moral standards

- **Teen pathologies will decline**:
  - Truancy
  - Substance abuse
  - Crime
  - Suicide
  - Unwed pregnancy

- Adults will welcome change in **teen sex** → will become **less matter-of-fact and starkly physical**, more **romantic and friendly**

- Trends apparent in affluent suburbs will also emerge in inner cities where peer-pressured boys show **more responsibility toward sexual (and parental) relationships**

### Music and Cultural Shift

- **Teen music** will become:
  - More **ballad-like, wholesome, and singable**
  - Top tunes appealing to **all generations**
  - On theme park rides: Millennial ears will hear bland **13er music** as **chaotic**
  - **Old Boomer classics** will sound **oddly ethereal and unpleasantly androgynous**

- From music to fashion to cinema, **adolescent culture will accentuate, even celebrate, sexual distinctions**

### Intergenerational Relations in Early 21st Century

- **13ers will have mellowing** effect on Millennials as young Civics develop positive impression of **Reactive peer personality**
- **G.I. recollection of 1920s era** (fun-loving Lost and strict Missionary teachers) offers illustration of what may lie in store

#### Millennial View of Boomers and 13ers

- Millennials will **respect Boomers as beacons** for the **"should-dos"** of life
- Will rely on **13ers as avuncular guides** to the **"want-to-dos"**
- Millennials will see their **next-elders as daring, puckish, full of mischief**
- In return, **13ers will see these kids as extremely "smart but naive"** — bit too optimistic for their own good and **in need of a lesson or two about real life**

#### Millennial Interest in 13er Culture

- College-age Millennials will be **fascinated by 13er cultural trends**
- Occasionally joining in **13er naughtiness** — but will try to do so **discreetly**, so as

<!-- p. 423 -->

### Millennials' Relationship with Boomers

- **Millennials remain kind to younger generations** getting better deals than 13ers at same age, continuing Boomer pattern of not disappointing high standards
- Youth civic engagement increases as **Millennials called upon for civic deeds**
- Community institutions (schools, libraries, churches, police) become more important in **child's life**
- **Scout programs expand**, old ones revitalized, new ones formed
- Boomers push **Millennial adolescents toward socially useful purposes**: studying, practicing, organizing

### Teen Employment and Education

- **Teen employment declines** by law and family fiat
- Teen employment sharing **new Boomer vision**: sanitized, laden with moral lessons
- Universities introduce **new government-aided tuition finance** linked to public service performance before/during/after college
- Around **year 2000**: wave of different freshmen descend on campuses showing **greater talent for**:
  - Student politics
  - Athletic teamwork
  - Math and science in classroom

### Millennials as Civic Problem-Solvers

- **Millennials cooperate government as benign, reliable means** of providing for their age bracket (vs. 13ers' helter-skelter marketplace shaped by rising 13ers)
- **Boom-era mandatory national service** puts millions of youths in uniform—compulsion Millennials won't mind as much as Boomers/13ers did
- They'll **seek opportunity to prove community service and earn public adulation**
- **Practical agenda**: Millennials find solution, organize, cooperate, share burdens, get job done
- Effectiveness and cheerfulness **will stun their elders**

### Generational Character

- First Millennials coming of age will seem **bland** to elders
- They won't waste effort on **reflecting on values or following spiritual impulses**—nor will Boomers ask them to
- **Aging Boomers gradually realize nurture style**: producing better **doers than feelers, rationalists than spiritualists**
- These kids bear **eerie resemblance to G.I.s** against whom Boomers rebelled in late 1960s
- Likeness won't bother most Boomers midlifers, who see in Millennials **what country needs to overcome adversity**
- Like old Awakeners who loved their Republican kids while lamenting Liberty, **Boomers develop better lifelong friendships with Millennials than with 13ers**
- **Relationships between older Idealists and younger Civics** ranked among warmest intergenerational bonds in American history

### Entering Rising Adulthood in a Crisis Era (2004-2025)

- Early Crisis era: **rising-adult Millennials (especially first wave) encounter economic and social hardship**
- Unlike 13ers, they emerge **undaunted**—thanks to:
  - Patience
  - Confidence
  - Powerful instinct

<!-- p. 424 -->

### Millennial End-Year and Civic Personality

- **Millennial end-year timing**: Former boundary between 1981-1982 cohorts, latter between 2002-2004 cohorts
- Both locations are estimates—likely need another four decades before drawing the Millennial end-year with precision (similar to 1910 uncertainty about G.I. end-year in late 1940s)

### Millennial Civic Peer Personality: Not Predetermined

**Two possible futures depend on crisis outcome:**

1. **Crisis unfolds badly**: Millennials become "a smart but hobbled generation" unable to realize idealist elders' agenda

2. **Crisis allows coalescence**: Millennials become genuine **Civic type** with:
   - More teamlike spirit and more likeability
   - More literalness in action than most Americans alive will have seen in young people
   - Attraction to global ideologies promising material utopias through collective action
   - Political coalescence as nation unifies
   - Potential for sudden party realignment strengthening mandate of aging Boom leaders

### Elderly Boomers' View of Millennials

- Boomers will see Millennials as "an effective instrument for saving the world"
- Having screamed against duty and discipline when young, **Boomers will now demand duty and discipline from post-adolescents**
- They will shower youthful heroes and heroines with praise and reward
- Rising Millennials will feel the intoxication of hubris, resisting elders (Boomers) they perceive as unwilling to relinquish private and material privilege
- Parallel: Young Republicans muzzled Tory Awakeners; young G.I.s voted laissez-faire Missionaries out of office
- Young Millennials will rise against perceived enemies of community solidarity and public action

### Millennial Crisis Mission

**Mission execution depends on crisis type:**

- **War**: Soldiers obey orders without complaint
- **Environmental danger/resource depletion**: Young scientists make historic breakthroughs
- **Economic crisis**: Youthful labor force becomes mighty engine of renewed American prosperity

**Key principle**: Millennials will carry out whatever crisis mission assigned—**as long as they can connect it with their own secular blueprint for progress**

**Outcome if crisis turns out well**: Millennials will be forever honored as **a generation of civic achievers**

<!-- p. 425 -->

### Entering Midlife in an Outer-Driven Era (2026-2047)

- When crisis passes and new **Outer-Driven era** dawns, age bias of public institutions will tilt far (perhaps too far) in direction of **Millennials**
- **Millennials** will become generation equated with investment in long-term future—much as government did in favor of **Republicans** in 1750s and **G.I.s** in late 1940s
- In politics, as sense of national community builds, **Millennial voters** may congeal into "end of ideology" generation whose political parties show little difference in style
- Meanwhile, they will solidify peer conformity by unmasking radicals who embraced "ism" in their eager youth (early-twenty-first-century equivalent of **Republican Jacobinism** or **G.I. communism**)
- Political culture of fortyish Millennials in 2030s will be highly **conformist**—only team players invited

#### The Circa-2030 National Mood

- **Millennials** will construct circa-2030 national mood reminiscent of post-World War II "**American High**"
- Rising leaders will feel obligation to complete unfinished agenda of revered **Boom elders**
- Institutions will strengthen, construction will boom, American society will substantially change its outward appearance
- In churches, ministers emphasize **social fellowship** over **spiritual self-discovery**
- In universities, brilliant minds feel in godlike control over nature
- Scientists will design (and taxpayers fund) grand projects glorifying **thinker-doer-builder**
- "Right-stuff" Millennials will command (and younger technicians copilot) manned space flights to nearest planets
- **Midlife parents and their children** (with old-fashioned 13ers looking on) will perceive themselves as distinctly "modern"
- Days of **V-8 engines and vacuum tubes** will seem as quaint in 2030s as steam turbines and telegraph lines did in 1950s

#### Gender Relations and Social Attitudes

- Like earlier **Civic generations**, fortyish Millennials will feel most comfortable with widely separated **sex roles**
- They may begin to view separate posturing of very old **Idealist women** as anachronistic—and look upon suspicious self-sufficiency of aging **13er women** as antisocial and possibly dangerous
- To chagrin of old feminists, Millennials will exalt **masculine** and criticize **feminine influence** on public life—and reverse in private life
- **Resurgent sexism** will limit life options of rising **Adaptive women**, planting seeds of mid-twenty-first-century **feminist renaissance**

#### Ethnic Loyalties and Diversity

- Thanks to Millennial team orientation, **ethnic loyalties** will weaken relative to sense of national community
- Applying circa-1990 definition, this is far and away most "**minority**" generation in American history
- But by middle of twenty-first century, very word "**minority**" will have odd ring to generation more inclined to **homogenize** than **pluralize**
- **Racial integration** [continues on next page]

<!-- p. 426 -->

### Entering Elderhood in an Awakening Era (2048-2069)

- **2040s prediction**: Vigorous veterans in their fifties may march down **Pennsylvania Avenue**, accompanied by parade floats carrying their instruments of valor
- Will celebrate inauguration of America's **first Millennial President**
- Message to other generations will echo **1961**: arrival of great and heroic Civic generation

**New "boom" crop watching from sidelines**:
- New (probably "boom") crop of kids raised indulgently and scientifically by **Millennial moms and dads**
- These kids will notice something a bit stale and unreflective in veterans' parade
- Warning: Within a few years, as busy Millennials undertake their grandest-ever projects, **fury of youth will erupt**

**Generational reversal by 2050s**:
- Sixtyish Millennials may find themselves on wrong side of **two-giant "generation gap"**
- Will reminisce of late 1960s, look back at what good children they were in 1990s
- Will puzzle over why their children cannot afford them same respect once shown to own Boomer parents
- After fires of new awakening have cooled and series of outer-world disappointments, **Millennials will retreat together into comfortable old age**
- Will wonder if their lifetime constructions can survive **rising generation of narcissists**

**Bushlike President scenario**:
- If **Bushlike President** stages his generation's final inaugural (could happen on January 20, 2069), old Millennial heroes by now in their seventies will march down Pennsylvania Avenue for last time
- Next President will come to power knowing about the **Crisis of 2020** only through a child's eye or from film clips
- When that happens, Americans of all ages will feel something missing

**Millennial Generation's unfathomably long reach**:
- Present-day capacity to reckon the future means Millennial Generation will have unfathomably long reach
- Perhaps a million will live to see **twenty-second century**
- Some will be around to celebrate arrival of babies who will live into **the twenty-third century**
- These future babies will grow up looking upon **John Kennedy** as distantly as Kennedy looked upon **Thomas Jefferson**
- Those born in a year that will then seem ancient (in **1910, 1930, 1950, or 1970**) can hardly imagine what world these future children might inherit
- "We can only guess at the great wonders they will see, the great deeds they will accomplish, the great truths"

<!-- p. 427 -->

- Future generations will also play their role in the **drama of American generations**
- The generational pageant has been **vast and magnificent**, with many acts and actors since **John Winthrop** first felt the hand of God
- Yet surely one with **even more acts and actors yet to come**

<!-- p. 428 -->

## Chapter 14: The Beginning of History

### Individual vs. Generational Connection to History

- Most individuals feel limited connection to the larger story of human progress
- Few are lucky enough to participate in great events
- Fewer still sense their personal acts make any appreciable difference
- Through generational membership, we all take part in **history-bending moments**
- Through **cross-generational relationships**, we communicate across eras of mind-bending length

### The Adams Family: A Generational Drama

- Each person stands at the apex of an unfolding **generational drama**, heir to the past and ancestor to the future

#### Charles Francis Adams Example

- **Charles Francis Adams**: U.S. ambassador to England during the Civil War, stood at center of an extraordinary family tree
- Published a ten-volume biography of his grandfather (a U.S. President)
- Compiled a twelve-volume diary of the notes of his father (also a President)
- Then saw one of his sons (a celebrated author) write a biography of him

#### Extended Family Lifespan Overlap

- **Charles' grandfather John** was born in 1735
- **Grandson Charles Francis III** died in 1954
- Both their lives overlapped by roughly two decades
- **Charles Francis Adams** was nurtured by an ancestor and gave nurture to an heir whose combined lifespans extended **220 years**

### Modern Cross-Generational Connections

- Setting aside unique career portfolios, the Adams family tree resembles most Americans today
- **Example of modern generational overlap**: Boomer woman, age 40 in 1990, whose grandmother was age 70 when she was born, and who has a 5-year-old daughter in kindergarten
- Suppose that child will also, at age 35, give birth to a daughter

<!-- p. 429 -->

### Generational Perspective on History and the Future

- Americans alive today share much in common with ancestors from **1910, 1845, 1750, or 1650**—all lived at the edge of the future, felt pride about days gone by, hope and anxiety about days to come
- Some generations pleased, others not, shaped by what they experienced and could teach the young
- Each generation had its own **"diagonal" connection** with events of its time, its own glimpse of the cycle, its own vision of the future
- Each encountered a crisis at some phase of life

**Pattern continuation into the 21st century:**
- No reason to expect pattern won't continue—except next time, any crisis will be accompanied by **long-unprecedented tragedy**
- The cycle teaches bad endings can take decades to build up in early phases, can be hard to foresee—hinging on how small children are nurtured, whether elder generations offer young a constructive mission

### Mankind's Rejuvenative Capacity

**Central lesson of the cycle:** Each generational type makes its own unique contribution to human progress—something its members alone, among the living, can provide in sufficient measure to keep civilization from veering toward disaster

**1990s outlook by generation:**
- In no less than decades gone by, the cycle will look to each living generation for something special
- **Surviving G.I.s:** civic example and protection against erosion of worldly endownments
- **Elder Silent:** it will ask an other-directed kindness
- **Midlife Boomers:** vision and values
- **Rising-adult 13ers:** pragmatism and defense of individual liberty
- **Young Millennials:** new civic energy and devotion to community

<!-- p. 430 -->

### The Vortex Moving Toward Boom and 13er Generations

- Two generations have especially important roles in the drama ahead: **G.I.s** (having mostly made their mark) and **Silent** (running out of time to make theirs)
- The **vortex of history** is inexorably moving toward the **Boom** and **13er** generations
- Less riding on them than once rode on **Franklin and Washington**, **Lincoln and Grant**, or **Roosevelt and Eisenhower**
- Scripts awaiting both generations are markedly at odds with what Americans now associate with their recent phases of life

### Future Generational Tests

- Future generations of Americans must rely on aging **Boomers** to build a very unyuppielike ethic of **community responsibility** and **principled self-sacrifice**
- Where their G.I. parents were heroes young, history warns Boomers to expect their greatest test **in old age**
- Future generations are counting on **13ers** to graduate from *Liar's Poker* and mellow into middle caretakers, **guardians of family life**, and **protectors against Idealist excess**
- Where the Silent hedged their bets in youth and took their chances in midlife, history warns 13ers to prepare for the opposite
- If Boomers and 13ers pursue their respective missions well, the **cycle of generations** will also be a **cycle of progress** for those who follow

### "For Ourselves and Our Posterity"

> "For ourselves and our posterity..." The Preamble to the United States Constitution includes these five words, a summons to treat the present and future as partners in human destiny.

- When reading (or writing) history, we naturally digress from remembrances of others to imagine future remembrances of ourselves
- Just as we are all heirs of ancestors we mostly admire, so too are we all ancestors to heirs whose admiration we should wish to earn
- Reflecting on the story of America's **eighteen generations**, we realize that all of us alive today were once "posterity" in the dim vision of times gone by
- Perhaps, we will remind ourselves of our sacred obligation to act as kindly toward the future as ancestral generations once did toward us

